And hopefully, as we get through the second quarter, we'll be in a better state to see where we are for the year. So hopefully, that answers your question. Since you're talking about the second quarter, and my memory failed me earlier, sorry. So Steve's question earlier also on -- if you're looking at Q1 versus Q2, just another point is FX, which is $0.13 benefit in Q1.

For the year, we still see that to be $0.15. Again, we'll see where currencies move as the world plays itself out. And then from a tax rate perspective, we were at 16.4% for the first quarter, and our plan is 20% to 21% for the year. So those are the other items I would talk about, John, as I talk about the second quarter and its overall impact.

